Detailed Description

Indicates success or failure of an OBEX operation.

This class defines an implicit conversion to BOOLEAN where 'TRUE' indicates success whereas 'FALSE' means that an error has occured. The actual obex response code can be obtained by GetObexResponseCode().

Default-constructed instances indicate an 'Unspecified' error. Use the named constructor Ok() to obtain an BtObexResponseCode object that means success.

Note: currently only Obex response codes needed by Basic Imaging are supported.
